# Technical Standards for Beauty by Raquel Nicole Website

## Architecture Requirements
- **Frontend:** Next.js with React, server-side rendering for SEO
- **Styling:** TailwindCSS with custom design tokens
- **State Management:** Context API for lightweight state
- **Animations:** Framer Motion for micro-interactions
- **Backend:** Node.js with Express, JWT authentication
- **Database:** PostgreSQL with Prisma ORM
- **Hosting:** Vercel (frontend), AWS/Heroku (backend)

## Performance Standards
- **Lighthouse Target:** 90+ across all metrics
- **Page Load:** < 1 second
- **Core Web Vitals:** LCP < 1s, TBT < 100ms, CLS < 0.1
- **Mobile-First:** Responsive design with 4-column mobile grid
- **Accessibility:** WCAG 2.1 AA compliance

## Code Quality Standards
- Use TypeScript for type safety
- Implement proper error handling and loading states
- Follow React best practices (hooks, functional components)
- Use semantic HTML for SEO and accessibility
- Implement proper SEO meta tags and structured data

## API Integration Standards
- **Square POS API:** Real-time bookings and payments
- **Authentication:** JWT tokens with bcrypt password hashing
- **Security:** HTTPS, input sanitization, rate limiting
- **Error Handling:** Graceful fallbacks and user-friendly messages

## Database Schema Requirements
- **Users:** id, name, email, phone, role
- **Services:** id, title, description, price, duration
- **Bookings:** id, user_id, service_id, date, time, status
- **Memberships:** id, user_id, tier, discount, points
- **Reviews:** id, user_id, rating, comment, created_at
- **Blog Posts:** id, title, content, author_id, created_at

## SEO Requirements
- Implement structured data for local business, services, reviews
- Optimize meta tags, title tags, and alt text
- Create keyword-rich service pages and blog content
- Ensure proper internal linking structure
- Implement Google Business Profile integration

## Security Standards
- PCI-DSS compliance (payments via Square)
- Input sanitization and XSS prevention
- Rate limiting on API endpoints
- Secure session management
- Data encryption in transit and at rest
